[
    {
        "text": "Hi, I’m Francis, ",
        "start": 6.294,
        "duration": 1.235
    },
    {
        "text": "the host of this show \"Cooking with Dog.\"",
        "start": 7.529,
        "duration": 3.002
    },
    {
        "text": "First, let’s make the batter.",
        "start": 20.072,
        "duration": 2.463
    },
    {
        "text": "Add the warm milk to the honey in a bowl.",
        "start": 23.103,
        "duration": 3.385
    },
    {
        "text": "Mix it evenly with a spatula.",
        "start": 28.238,
        "duration": 2.851
    },
    {
        "text": "Add the egg ",
        "start": 35.775,
        "duration": 1.524
    },
    {
        "text": "and lightly beat with a hand mixer.",
        "start": 38.283,
        "duration": 2.951
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, add the sugar.  ",
        "start": 46.114,
        "duration": 1.519
    },
    {
        "text": "Continue to whip the mixture at a medium speed ",
        "start": 49.951,
        "duration": 3.265
    },
    {
        "text": "until the color turns white, ",
        "start": 53.216,
        "duration": 1.934
    },
    {
        "text": "and it reaches a soft peak stage.",
        "start": 55.15,
        "duration": 2.974
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, switch to a low speed ",
        "start": 62.165,
        "duration": 2.506
    },
    {
        "text": "and break any relatively large air bubbles.",
        "start": 64.671,
        "duration": 3.585
    },
    {
        "text": "Next, add the baking powder ",
        "start": 73.56,
        "duration": 2.002
    },
    {
        "text": "to the bread flour and mix.",
        "start": 75.562,
        "duration": 2.734
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, place the powder into a mesh strainer.",
        "start": 81.348,
        "duration": 3.549
    },
    {
        "text": "And sieve it into the egg mixture.",
        "start": 85.95,
        "duration": 2.968
    },
    {
        "text": "Lightly mix at a low speed.",
        "start": 92.125,
        "duration": 2.57
    },
    {
        "text": "Avoid overmixing ",
        "start": 94.943,
        "duration": 1.46
    },
    {
        "text": "otherwise the castella will lose its fluffy texture.  ",
        "start": 96.403,
        "duration": 3.836
    },
    {
        "text": "When all the flour is moistened, ",
        "start": 100.627,
        "duration": 2.233
    },
    {
        "text": "turn off the mixer.",
        "start": 102.86,
        "duration": 1.935
    },
    {
        "text": "And now, let’s make the baby castella.",
        "start": 107.543,
        "duration": 3.081
    },
    {
        "text": "Coat the takoyaki mold with vegetable oil.",
        "start": 112.476,
        "duration": 3.109
    },
    {
        "text": "Turn the heat to low ",
        "start": 117.472,
        "duration": 1.702
    },
    {
        "text": "and place the batter into the molds.",
        "start": 119.174,
        "duration": 2.601
    },
    {
        "text": "Each mold should be about 7 to 8 parts full.",
        "start": 122.214,
        "duration": 3.767
    },
    {
        "text": "The batter is light and foamy ",
        "start": 126.202,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "so it’s a little difficult to place it into the molds ",
        "start": 128.422,
        "duration": 3.513
    },
    {
        "text": "but you will be rewarded ",
        "start": 131.935,
        "duration": 1.383
    },
    {
        "text": "with soft and fluffy castella later.",
        "start": 133.318,
        "duration": 3.452
    },
    {
        "text": "Cover with a lid.",
        "start": 138.554,
        "duration": 1.872
    },
    {
        "text": "When the top is still wet and the small air bubbles ",
        "start": 145.967,
        "duration": 2.938
    },
    {
        "text": "on the surface begin to break, ",
        "start": 148.905,
        "duration": 2.384
    },
    {
        "text": "combine 2 pieces together and lightly press them.",
        "start": 151.289,
        "duration": 3.749
    },
    {
        "text": "If the surface is dry, ",
        "start": 155.89,
        "duration": 1.85
    },
    {
        "text": "they will not stick together so please do it quickly.",
        "start": 157.74,
        "duration": 4.02
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, rotate the baby castella to brown the sides.",
        "start": 167.147,
        "duration": 3.815
    },
    {
        "text": "Cover again and cook the inside on low heat.",
        "start": 174.283,
        "duration": 3.683
    },
    {
        "text": "Unlike suzu castella, ",
        "start": 180.21,
        "duration": 1.696
    },
    {
        "text": "baby castella is entirely browned.",
        "start": 181.906,
        "duration": 2.934
    },
    {
        "text": "It is often sold as a snack at festivals ",
        "start": 184.991,
        "duration": 3.469
    },
    {
        "text": "and known by a variety of names, ",
        "start": 188.46,
        "duration": 2.301
    },
    {
        "text": "depending on the area of Japan.",
        "start": 190.761,
        "duration": 2.701
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, they are ready.",
        "start": 195.196,
        "duration": 1.933
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the baby castella onto a cooling rack.",
        "start": 199.673,
        "duration": 3.436
    },
    {
        "text": "Next, we will show you ",
        "start": 204.41,
        "duration": 1.501
    },
    {
        "text": "how to make the suzu castella.",
        "start": 205.911,
        "duration": 2.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Clean the plate and re-oil the mold.",
        "start": 208.879,
        "duration": 2.934
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, place the batter into the molds.",
        "start": 214.887,
        "duration": 3.105
    },
    {
        "text": "The heat should remain on low but this time, ",
        "start": 218.372,
        "duration": 3.236
    },
    {
        "text": "each mold should be completely full.",
        "start": 221.608,
        "duration": 2.801
    },
    {
        "text": "Cover.",
        "start": 225.861,
        "duration": 1.317
    },
    {
        "text": "When the bottom of the castella is ",
        "start": 233.447,
        "duration": 1.533
    },
    {
        "text": "thoroughly browned, flip the pieces over.",
        "start": 234.98,
        "duration": 3.852
    },
    {
        "text": "The half browned round shape ",
        "start": 239.4,
        "duration": 1.867
    },
    {
        "text": "looks like a bell, doesn’t it?",
        "start": 241.267,
        "duration": 2.114
    },
    {
        "text": "Suzu means bell in Japanese ",
        "start": 243.839,
        "duration": 2.402
    },
    {
        "text": "so that is why we call these suzu castella.",
        "start": 246.241,
        "duration": 4.167
    },
    {
        "text": "Reduce the heat to the lowest possible heat.",
        "start": 251.96,
        "duration": 3.228
    },
    {
        "text": "Cover and cook the inside ",
        "start": 256.767,
        "duration": 2.248
    },
    {
        "text": "but try not to brown the bottom.",
        "start": 259.015,
        "duration": 2.368
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, they are ready.",
        "start": 263.668,
        "duration": 2.084
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the suzu castella onto the cooling rack.",
        "start": 269.004,
        "duration": 3.119
    },
    {
        "text": "When the suzu castella are slightly cooled, ",
        "start": 274.646,
        "duration": 2.795
    },
    {
        "text": "place them into a plastic bag with sugar.",
        "start": 277.441,
        "duration": 3.168
    },
    {
        "text": "Slightly cooling the castella ",
        "start": 281.376,
        "duration": 1.802
    },
    {
        "text": "will help them to coat thinly and evenly, ",
        "start": 283.178,
        "duration": 3.034
    },
    {
        "text": "making them more presentable.",
        "start": 286.212,
        "duration": 2.218
    },
    {
        "text": "These castella are still fluffy and delicious ",
        "start": 292.097,
        "duration": 3.103
    },
    {
        "text": "when cooled or even the next day ",
        "start": 295.2,
        "duration": 2.774
    },
    {
        "text": "and they can be stored in the freezer.",
        "start": 297.974,
        "duration": 2.394
    },
    {
        "text": "Alternatively, you can make slightly ",
        "start": 310.579,
        "duration": 2.218
    },
    {
        "text": "different versions by adding sweet bean paste ",
        "start": 312.797,
        "duration": 3.439
    },
    {
        "text": "or melting cheese as a filling.",
        "start": 316.236,
        "duration": 2.747
    },
    {
        "text": "Good luck in the kitchen!",
        "start": 318.983,
        "duration": 1.417
    }
]